,"timestamp":1777109601759},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! Line 540 has this:\n```\n    echo '    [1] M-fM-/M-^OM-eM-$M-)M-eM-^GM-^LM-fM-^YM-( 2:00  (M-fM-^NM-(M-hM-^MM-^P)'\n```\n\nWait, that looks wrong. The cat -A shows the raw bytes. The Chinese characters are being shown as multi-byte sequences. But line 540 is a single-quoted string that starts with `'    [1]` but doesn't have a closing `'`. \n\nLooking at this line:\n\n\n```\n    echo '    [1] M-fM-/M-^OM-eM-$M-)M-eM-^GM-^LM-fM-^YM-( 2:00  (M-fM-^NM-(M-hM-^MM-^P)'\n```\n\nThe line ends with a single quote after `M-hM-^MM-^P)`. So that looks correctly closed.\n\nBut wait - looking at line 539:\n```\n    echo \"  M-hM-/M-7M-iM-^@M-^IM-fM-^KM-)M-iM-\"M-^DM-hM-.M->M-fM-^HM-^VM-hM-^GM-*M-eM-.M-^ZM-dM-9M-^I$\n```\n\nThis is a double-quoted string. Let me count the quotes carefully. The line starts with `echo \"` and I need to find where it closes.\n\nActually, I'm noticing the heredoc at line 611 opens with `<<EOF` and closes at line 656 with `EOF`. But I should verify there isn't another unclosed heredoc earlier in the file that's causing issues.\n\nLet me step back and search for any unclosed double-quoted strings directly using grep to pinpoint the problem.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qj6q5br2yccf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\ncontent = open('/workspace/projects/workspace/healthcheck-skill/scripts/cron-manager.sh').read()\n# Remove comments\nlines = content.split('\\n')\nin_comment = False\ncode_lines = []\nfor line in lines:\n    stripped = line.strip()\n    if stripped.startswith('#'):\n        continue\n    code_lines.append(line)\n\ncode = '\\n'.join(code_lines)\n# Count unescaped double quotes\ndq_count = code.count('\\\"') - code.count('\\\\\\\"')\nprint(f'Double quotes: {dq_count}')\n\n# Also check heredocs\nimport re\nheredoc_pattern = r'<<[\\'\\\"]?(\\w+)'\nmatches = list(re.finditer(r'<<-?\\s*[\\'\\\"]?(\\w+)', code))\nprint(f'Heredocs found: {len(matches)}')\nfor m in matches:\n    delim = m.group(1)\n    # Count opening and closing heredocs\n    opens = len(re.findall(rf'<<[\\'\\\"]?\\s*{re.escape(delim)}', code))\n    closes = code.count(delim)\n    print(f'  {delim}: {opens} opens, {closes} closes')\n\"\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"coze","model":"auto","usage":{"input":66830,"output":1069,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67899,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777109601762,"responseId":"063bbd62ca2537772780c94eaa224d58"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qj6q5br2yccf_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Double quotes: 0\nHeredocs found: 4\n  EOF: 4 opens, 8 closes\n  EOF: 4 opens, 8 closes\n  EOF: 4 opens, 8 closes\n  EOF: 4 opens, 8 closes"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":57,"aggregated":"Double quotes: 0\nHeredocs found: 4\n  EOF: 4 opens, 8 closes\n  EOF: 4 opens, 8 closes\n  EOF: 4 opens, 8 closes\n  EOF: 4 opens, 8 closes","cwd":"/workspace/projects/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777109622367},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The double quote count is 0! That means there's a missing opening or closing double quote somewhere. Let me debug more carefully.\n\nActually, `0` means the count of unescaped double quotes is even (matching pairs). But wait - the python script subtracted escaped quotes... let me check.\n\nActually, the issue might be that the Chinese text contains characters that look like `\"` or `\"` (curly quotes) vs `\"` (ASCII straight quote). Let me check.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qxah2o7oh8ws_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\ncontent = open('/workspace/projects/workspace/healthcheck-skill/scripts/cron-manager.sh', 'rb').read()\n# Find non-ASCII double quote characters\nimport re\n# Look for curly quotes (Unicode left/right double quotation marks)\ncurly_left = b'\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x9c'   # U+201C\ncurly_right = b'\\\\xe2\\\\x80\\\\x9d'  # U+201D\nstraight = b'\\\"'\npositions = []\nfor i, b in enumerate(content):\n    if b == 0x22:  # straight quote\n        line_num = content[:i].count(b'\\\\n') + 1\n        positions.append((line_num, 'straight'))\n        \nprint(f'Found {len(positions)} double quotes')\nprint(f'First 10: {positions[:10]}')\nprint(f'Last 10: {positions[-10:]}')\n\"\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"coze","model":"auto","usage":{"input":826,"output":424,"cacheRead":66747,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67997,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777109622370,"responseId":"063bbd76deee1ce9dbad63b1b2ab2367"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qxah2o7oh8ws_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found 563 double quotes\nFirst 10: [(10, 'straight'), (10, 'straight'), (29, 'straight'), (29, 'straight'), (29, 'straight'), (29, 'straight'), (29, 'straight'), (29, 'straight'), (30, 'straight'), (30, 'straight')]\nLast 10: [(704, 'straight'), (704, 'straight'), (706, 'straight'), (706, 'straight'), (733, 'straight'), (733, 'straight'), (735, 'straight'), (735, 'straight'), (739, 'straight'), (739, 'straight')]"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":39,"aggregated":"Found 563 double quotes\nFirst 10: [(10, 'straight'), (10, 'straight'), (29, 'straight'), (29, 'straight'), (29, 'straight'), (29, 'straight'), (29, 'straight'), (29, 'straight'), (30, 'straight'), (30, 'straight')]\nLast 10: [(704, 'straight'), (704, 'straight'), (706, 'straight'), (706, 'straight'), (733, 'straight'), (733, 'straight'), (735, 'straight'), (735, 'straight'), (739, 'straight'), (739, 'straight')]","cwd":"/workspace/projects/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777109633084},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"563 is an odd number! There should be an even number of double quotes. So there IS a missing quote somewhere. Let me find which line has the odd quote.\n\nLet me count quotes per line.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qiab6fs4gecm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\ncontent = open('/workspace/projects/workspace/healthcheck-skill/scripts/cron-manager.sh', 'rb').read()\nlines = content.decode('utf-8', errors='replace').split('\\n')\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines, 1):\n    # Count unescaped double quotes\n    count = 0\n    j = 0\n    while j < len(line):\n        if line[j] == '\\\\\\\\':\n            j += 2\n            continue\n        if line[j] == '\\\"':\n            count += 1\n        j += 1\n    if count % 2 != 0:\n        print(f'Line {i} (odd={count}): {repr(line[:80])}')\n\"\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"coze","model":"auto","usage":{"input":404,"output":265,"cacheRead":67643,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68312,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777109633087,"responseId":"063bbd81138008d770f8b929f8f4aa33"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qiab6fs4gecm_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Line 277 (odd=3): '    local new_cron=\"${current_cron:+$current_cron\"$\\'\\\\n\\'}\"'"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":29,"aggregated":"Line 277 (odd=3): '    local new_cron=\"${current_cron:+$current_cron\"$\\'\\\\n\\'}\"'","cwd":"/workspace/projects/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777109640221},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! Line 277 has 3 double quotes (odd). Let me look at that line more carefully.The line is:\n```\n    local new_cron=\"${current_cron:+$current_cron\"$\\'\\n\\'}\"\n```This is trying to append a newline character to the cron content, but the quoting is wrong. The intended line should be:\n```bash\n    local new_cron=\"${current_cron:+$current_cron}\"$'\\n'\n```or:\n```bash\n    local new_cron=\"${current_cron:+$current_cron}\"$'\\\\n'\n```Wait, let me look at the original code more carefully.\n\n\nLooking at the original, I need to properly escape the newline in the heredoc. The issue is that using `\"$\\'\\n\\'\"` creates three separate double quotes instead of properly concatenating the newline character. The cleanest approach is to just use `$'\\n'` on its own line to add the newline to the cron expression, which avoids the quoting mess entirely. I need to step back and look at the original code structure to understand how it's actually building the cron configuration with the marker and newline. I need to step back and look at the original line more carefully—let me retrieve it fresh from the file to see what I'm actually working with.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h59ou2n6u4ad_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '270,282p' /workspace/projects/workspace/healthcheck-skill/scripts/cron-manager.sh"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"coze","model":"auto","usage":{"input":223,"output":579,"cacheRead":68091,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68893,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777109640225,"responseId":"063bbd8854ec45211ab479ed9572a5e4"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h59ou2n6u4ad_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"remove_cron_job\n\n    # 添加新任务\n    local current_cron\n    current_cron=$(get_cron_jobs)\n\n    # 添加注释和任务\n    local new_cron=\"${current_cron:+$current_cron\"$'\\n'}\"\n    new_cron=\"${new_cron}${CRON_MARKER} $CRON_LABEL\"$'\\n'\n    new_cron=\"${new_cron}${cron_cmd}\"\n\n    # 写入 crontab\n    echo \"$new_cron\" | crontab -"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"remove_cron_job\n\n    # 添加新任务\